OL,3,COver #2bn spent taking children to
OL,4,Cschool: The numbers behind the SEND
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,FThat is because of a huge increase in
OL,8,Fkids with EHCPs in mainstream schools.
OL,10,FIn its report, the IFS says that the
OL,11,F"vast majority of new pupils with
OL,12,FEHCPs" are educated in non-specialist
OL,13,Fschools - despite the increased
OL,14,Fnumbers accessing private provision.
OL,16,FHow will the government bring costs
OL,17,Fdown?
OL,19,FIt is this finding in particular that
OL,20,Fpoints to the challenge right at the
OL,21,Fheart of SEND reform.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/19
