OL,7,FThat has left most councils spending
OL,8,Fmore money than they have, racking up
OL,9,Fa deficit.
OL,11,FAccording to campaign group Special
OL,12,FNeeds Jungle, nine in 10 councils have
OL,13,Fdeficit at a combined total of #6.6bn.
OL,15,FThe OBR said in November, that if the
OL,16,Fcurrent situation didn't change, that
OL,17,Fcould rise to #14bn by 2028, a figure
OL,18,Fwhich provoked fears that councils
OL,19,Fwould be financially obliterated.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/19
